<A>__{right, that's it then. they leave him, walking forward along the deck. hartley puts his violin to his chin and bows the first notes of "nearer my god to thee". one by one the band memebers turn, hearing the lonely melody. without a word they walk back and take their places. they join in with hartley, filling out the sound so that it reaches all over the ship on this still night. the vocalist begins: "if in my dreams i be, nearer my god to thee..."}
